article.headline: Oral Roberts 79, Chicago St 76
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Caleb Green and Ken Tutt scored 23 points each as Oral Roberts beat Chicago State 79-76 on Saturday night. Aided by a number of second-half fouls called against Chicago State (3-13, 2-4 Mid-Con), the Golden Eagles (14-4, 5-1) overcame a first-half deficit of 33-32. Green accounted for most of the Golden Eagles' free throw points, shooting 13-of-15 from the line. He also led Oral Roberts in assists with six, and tied Larry Owens for a team-high eight rebounds. Deji Akindele had a double-double for Chicago State, scoring 19 points and pulling down 13 rebounds. Akindele also had four blocks.
